<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Add Expense</title>
<style type="text/css">
.underline{
	text-decoration: underline;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div>
	<b>Fields on <span class="underline">Expense Screen</span></b><br/>
	<b>Date:</b> Auto populated to today’s date but you can change. <br/>
	<b>Amount:</b>  Numeric value of the money spent<br/>
	<b>Description:</b> Free text field to enter your notes<br/>
	<b>Mode*:</b>  Enter which credit card, bank transfer, cash<br/>
	<b>Expense Category*:</b>  Broad categorization like Office Supplies, Cell phone bills, Petrol and so on
	<br/><br/>
	<b>Buttons</b><br/>
	<b>Take Picture:</b> This button invokes onboard camera app. Click the image and hit Save at the bottom to come back to the Expense Screen.<br/>
	<b>Save</b> to save the record you  just entered.<br/>
	<b>After Saving</b> you can enter new expense or review the previous expense records through the navigation buttons on the<br/> 
	Go back to go to Home screen.<br/><br/>
	
	*Fields that have memory. If you enter data once, it will remember that entry for future records so that you don’t have to enter the entire term next time.
	<br/>
</div>
</body>
</html>